 <item rdf:about="https://maritime-union.com/job/222782/">
  <description>&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; United States of America (USA)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&#9;&lt;p&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-family:Arial,sans-serif; max-width:660px&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;Towage &amp;nbsp;&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp; &lt;span class=&quot;caps&quot;&gt;USA&lt;/span&gt; &amp;nbsp;&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp; 6 weeks &amp;nbsp;&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp; US / B1 Visa required&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&#10;&lt;div style=&quot;border-top:1px solid #e0e0e0; margin-bottom:14px; padding-top:14px&quot;&gt;&#10;&lt;p&gt;Multicat vessel operating in the &lt;span class=&quot;caps&quot;&gt;USA&lt;/span&gt; under a &amp;lt;200 GT UK Master CoC. The position is straightforward in scope &amp;mdash; you take command, you lead the deck operations, and you work with a crew that knows its job. The owner is looking for someone who can board ready to work, not someone who needs time to find their footing. Six-week contract with a defined start &amp;mdash; useful for a Master who plans ahead and keeps documentation current.&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&lt;/div&gt;&#10;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&#10;&#9;&lt;p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&#9;&lt;li&gt;🎉 Valid UK Master CoC &amp;mdash; &amp;lt;200 GT&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&#9;&lt;li&gt;🆕 Valid US / B1 Visa &amp;mdash; mandatory&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&#9;&lt;li&gt;📋 All &lt;span class=&quot;caps&quot;&gt;STCW&lt;/span&gt; certificates current&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&#9;&lt;li&gt;⚓ Multicat experience required&lt;/li&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&#10;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#10;&#10;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contact us!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://maritime-union.com/job/222782/&quot;&gt;Apply to this job&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;</description>
  <link>https://maritime-union.com/job/222782/</link>
